        "subject": "LU-11205 mdd: process mixing changelog records",
        "message": "LU-11205 mdd: process mixing changelog records\n\nA changelog subsystem assigns index and adds a new records\nto the end of llog. There is no synchronization to combine\nboth operation. And a llog records order doesn't fit with an\nindex order, and it could be mixed. But a changelog logic\nbase on index order.\n\nThe patch changes changelog processing logic to work with\na mixing records. Also cr_index assignment is moved after\ntaking transaction handle, this guarantee that mixing\nrecords beelong to a single transaction.\n\nThe patch adds 160j sanity, to check that reordered recordes\nat changelog could be canceled.\n\nCray-bug-id: LUS-7583\nSigned-off-by: Alexander Boyko <c17825@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ib6c83fd965511678c0f3fef7f13337a9107c7c74\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
